India Is Confident of Meeting Share Sale Target, Gopalan Says

-- B y   A n t o   A n t o n y
-- 
2011-09-16T05:16:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/india-is-confident-of-meeting-share-sale-target-gopalan-says.html
The Indian government is confident
of meeting its target to raise 400 billion rupees selling shares
in state-run companies, R. Gopalan, secretary in the Department
of Economic Affairs in the finance ministry, said in an
interview today.  India will stick to its borrowing target for the year,
Gopalan said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anto Antony in  New Delhi  at 
